In the last decade, we have witnessed PhDs across the disciplines being awarded on the basis of publication.A single-authored paper in international peer-reviewed journals is evidence of this experience Writing a thesis is the last task that a PhD candidate performs before being awarded the degree. Universities in the past centuries encouraged a system where papers are written only after a PhD thesis is done.
The embargo is then placed on the thesis and only the title, abstract, and citation information is released to the public. The full text is hidden from the public for a period of time. The rules governing the embargoes varies from one university to another.



