 Articles published in internationally reviewed journals are an important aspect of research jobs, grants, and post-doctoral fellowships. While we can state many of these benefits from PhD by publications, we do not have sufficient data to justify the impact of this kind of researchers compared to those who are awarded a PhD without a single publication.
This idea, therefore, invites the scholarly community at large to have this conversation on the diversity of doctorates and how they will influence the market trends.
The critics of PhD by publication argue that both the supervisor and the institution have relinquished their responsibility to journals to maintain standards and improve the PhD work. The examination of a thesis based on papers is biased since the scores are based on where the articles were published rather than the work itself.
English and Kiswahili
This requires developing a new set of policies to guide on assessment or examining the new model of the thesis. It’s also time PhDs were written in both English and Kiswahili. The move will create a greater impact on society as the outcome of the thesis is spread to the general public. This will also accelerate the growth of the Kiswahili language in research and in scientific writings.



